modules.description: This module implements an immutable set abstraction for ordered elements, supporting creation, union, intersection, and difference operations alongside element-wise transformations and membership queries. It operates on sets of elements with a total ordering, enabling efficient structural manipulations and ordered traversals via iterators, folds, and sequence conversions. Typical applications include managing disjoint collections, performing set algebra, or processing ordered data with functional pipelines that require persistence across modifications.

This module defines parameters for configuring erasure coding schemes, specifically supporting operations to validate and construct parameter sets with constraints on data blocks, drop counts, and systematic encoding. It works with a parameter type `t` and an error type describing invalid configurations. Concrete use cases include setting up coding parameters for data transmission or storage systems requiring fault tolerance.
